BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 580 Td (A sequence in coding means the ORDER in which instructions happen. Order) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 562 Td (matters a LOT! Think about it: 'Put on socks, then put on shoes' works) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 544 Td (great. But 'Put on shoes, then put on socks' is impossible! In coding, if) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 526 Td (you put instructions in the wrong order, the program breaks or does) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 508 Td (something unexpected. Every program you use runs line by line in sequence.) Tj ET
BT 0.1 g /F2 12 Tf 72 465 Td (KEY CONCEPT:) Tj ET
BT 0.3 g /F4 11 Tf 90 445 Td (The computer reads code from top to bottom, one line at a time. If step 3) Tj ET
BT 0.3 g /F4 11 Tf 90 427 Td (needs information from step 2, step 2 MUST come first.) Tj ET

endstream
