BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 238.8 670 Td (Loops: Repeat!) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 580 Td (A loop is a set of instructions that repeats over and over. Without loops,) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 562 Td (you would have to write the same code hundreds of times! Imagine telling) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 544 Td (someone to 'clap 100 times.' Would you write 'clap' 100 times? No! You) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 526 Td (would say 'repeat clapping 100 times.' That is a loop. Loops can repeat a) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 508 Td (set number of times, or keep going until something happens.) Tj ET
BT 0.1 g /F2 12 Tf 72 465 Td (KEY CONCEPT:) Tj ET
BT 0.3 g /F4 11 Tf 90 445 Td (Types: FOR loops repeat a specific number of times. WHILE loops repeat) Tj ET
BT 0.3 g /F4 11 Tf 90 427 Td (until a condition changes. INFINITE loops never stop \(usually a bug!\).) Tj ET

endstream
